    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the boot up the shift lever shaft and remove (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300778">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300778" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300778" filename="../figg13/G1300778.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 78. Slide Boot Up Shift Lever Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With housing bottom facing up, secure the assembly in a vise (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300779">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300779" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300779" filename="../figg13/G1300779.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 79. Secure Assembly in Vise</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use large screwdriver to twist between the spring and housing, forcing the spring from
                    under the housing lugs (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300779">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer, and gear shift lever from the housing tower.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In models so equipped, remove the nut and washer from the housing bore.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and inspect the spade pin from the housing; replace if necessary (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300780">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300780" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300780" filename="../figg13/G1300780.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 80. Remove and Inspect Spade Pin</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the O-ring in the housing groove; replace if necessary (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300780">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
